From: Paolo Abeni <pabeni@redhat.com>
Date: Thu, 28 Sep 2017 15:51:36 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] IPv4: early demux can return an error code
References: bnc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 4.13.6
Git-commit: 7487449c86c65202b3b725c4524cb48dd65e4e6f

[ Upstream commit 7487449c86c65202b3b725c4524cb48dd65e4e6f ]

Currently no error is emitted, but this infrastructure will
used by the next patch to allow source address validation
for mcast sockets.
Since early demux can do a route lookup and an ipv4 route
lookup can return an error code this is consistent with the
current ipv4 route infrastructure.

Signed-off-by: Paolo Abeni <pabeni@redhat.com>
